  "articleSummary": "The article argues that AI agents become truly useful only when integrated with business systems via the **Model Context Protocol (MCP)**, a standardized framework that eliminates the need for custom API wrappers. It frames the integration problem as a critical bottleneck, comparing MCP’s role to USB-C’s unification of device connectivity. Key points include MCP’s ability to unify access to tools like Salesforce, Jira, and Google Maps through a single protocol layer, Mastra’s implementation of MCP with dynamic tool injection and per-user authentication, and code examples demonstrating seamless agent-tool interactions. The tone is tutorial and analytical, targeting developers building multi-tenant AI agents who need scalable, secure integrations. Recurring metaphors include USB-C standardization and “hands/eyes” for agents.",
